Additional Terms

BurpMax is a security testing tool. Use of this software is subject to the
following additional conditions:

1. Authorised use only. You may only use BurpMax against systems and
   applications for which you have explicit written authorisation to conduct
   security testing. Unauthorised use against systems you do not own or do
   not have permission to test is prohibited and may be illegal under the
   Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA), the Computer Misuse Act (CMA),
   and equivalent legislation in your jurisdiction.

2. No warranty for security findings. The author makes no representation
   that BurpMax will identify all vulnerabilities in a tested system.
   Security assessments conducted using BurpMax should be part of a
   comprehensive security programme and not relied upon as the sole means
   of identifying security weaknesses.

3. Responsible disclosure. If you discover vulnerabilities in third-party
   systems using BurpMax, you are encouraged to follow responsible
   disclosure practices and notify the affected organisation before
   publishing any findings.

4. No liability. In no event shall the author be liable for any damages,
   legal consequences, or other adverse outcomes arising from the use or
   misuse of this software.

These additional terms supplement the MIT licence above and do not restrict
the rights granted therein for lawful, authorised use.
